    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <opener> 
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Dover, Delaware,</name>
                    <date when="1875-04-04">April 4, 1875</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Friend,</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>Again I take the time &amp; <choice><sic>privlege</sic><corr>privilege</corr></choice> of 
                <choice><sic>droping</sic><corr>dropping</corr></choice> a few lines to tell you that we 
                have not forgotten you &amp; want to hear from you.<ptr target="nyp.00396_n1b"/> We have 
                had a son <choice><sic>borned</sic><corr>born</corr></choice> since we heard from you 
                &amp; We call him Walter Whitman Millis<ptr target="nyp.00396_n2"/> in <choice><sic>honer</sic><corr>honor</corr></choice> 
                to you for Love for you.</p>
            <p>How I would like to see your dear old face once more. Times is very hard here, &amp; money 
                is very scarce. Hoping to hear from you soon.</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>We remain yours with love</salute>
            </closer>
        </body>
    </text>
